---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout>
  <!-- CONTENT GOES HERE-->
  <main class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <!-- SECTION 1: The Problem (Agitate) -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
          Your Dog Isn't "Bad." Your Dog Is Overwhelmed.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Every walk feels like a war zone.<br />
          Another dog appears, and your stomach drops because you <em>know</em> what's
          coming.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div
        class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-8 rounded-r-2xl mb-8"
      >
        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Here's what's actually happening:
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl font-bold text-red-800 mb-6">
          Your dog's nervous system is stuck in survival mode.
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          The lunging, barking, spinning — it's not disobedience. It's panic.
          And most training advice makes it worse by:
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1"
              fill="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 20 20"
            >
              <path
                fill-rule="evenodd"
                d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zM8.707 7.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414L8.586 10l-1.293 1.293a1 1 0 101.414 1.414L10 11.414l1.293 1.293a1 1 0 001.414-1.414L11.414 10l1.293-1.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L10 8.586 8.707 7.293z"
                clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
            </svg>
            <span class="text-gray-900"
              ><strong>Pushing you closer</strong> than your dog can handle</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1"
              fill="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 20 20"
            >
              <path
                fill-rule="evenodd"
                d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zM8.707 7.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414L8.586 10l-1.293 1.293a1 1 0 101.414 1.414L10 11.414l1.293 1.293a1 1 0 001.414-1.414L11.414 10l1.293-1.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L10 8.586 8.707 7.293z"
                clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
            </svg>
            <span class="text-gray-900"
              ><strong>Telling you to "just ignore it"</strong> (which solves nothing)</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1"
              fill="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 20 20"
            >
              <path
                fill-rule="evenodd"
                d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zM8.707 7.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414L8.586 10l-1.293 1.293a1 1 0 101.414 1.414L10 11.414l1.293 1.293a1 1 0 001.414-1.414L11.414 10l1.293-1.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L10 8.586 8.707 7.293z"
                clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
            </svg>
            <span class="text-gray-900"
              ><strong>Giving vague advice</strong> like "stay calm" without tools
              to actually DO it</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1"
              fill="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 20 20"
            >
              <path
                fill-rule="evenodd"
                d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zM8.707 7.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414L8.586 10l-1.293 1.293a1 1 0 101.414 1.414L10 11.414l1.293 1.293a1 1 0 001.414-1.414L11.414 10l1.293-1.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L10 8.586 8.707 7.293z"
                clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
            </svg>
            <span class="text-gray-900"
              ><strong>Skipping the science</strong> of threshold, distance, and nervous
              system regulation</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-red-200">
          <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">The truth?</p>
          <p class="text-xl text-red-900 font-bold">
            You can't train a dog who's over threshold. You're fighting biology.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">
            And every failed walk reinforces the explosive behavior you're
            trying to stop.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 2: The Solution -->
    <section
      class="mb-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-blue-100 py-16 px-4 rounded-3xl"
    >
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
          What If You Had a Step-By-Step Blueprint?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 mb-4">
          Not generic advice. Not YouTube clips. An actual <strong
            >protocol</strong
          > used by professional behavior specialists.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-lg mb-8">
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-700 mb-4">
            The Reactive Dog Reset Planner
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            gives you the <strong
              >exact distance formulas, game-based training phases, and
              real-world walking scenarios</strong
            > to transform reactive behavior — without guesswork.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 italic">
          This isn't obedience training. This is <strong
            >nervous system regulation, threshold management, and classical
            conditioning</strong
          > — the same protocols we use in our Board & Train programs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 3: What's Inside -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Inside This Free Guide, You'll Get:
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          520 paragraphs of niche-level, CPDT-aligned reactive dog training.
          Zero fluff. All science.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">
        <!-- Benefit 1 -->
        <div
          class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-md border-l-4 border-blue-500 hover:shadow-xl transition"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0">
              <svg
                class="w-8 h-8 text-blue-500"
                fill="currentColor"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
              >
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Distance & Threshold Formula
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Know <em>exactly</em> when you're too close, when to increase difficulty,
                and how to measure progress with Green/Yellow/Red Zone markers.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Benefit 2 -->
        <div
          class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-md border-l-4 border-blue-500 hover:shadow-xl transition"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0">
              <svg
                class="w-8 h-8 text-blue-500"
                fill="currentColor"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
              >
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                6 Progressive Training Phases (Weeks 1–15+)
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Foundation Engagement → Trigger Awareness → Active
                Desensitization → Duration & Complexity → Real-World Proofing →
                Maintenance. Each phase builds on the last — no skipping ahead.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Benefit 3 -->
        <div
          class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-md border-l-4 border-blue-500 hover:shadow-xl transition"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0">
              <svg
                class="w-8 h-8 text-blue-500"
                fill="currentColor"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
              >
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                17 Training Games That Actually Work
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Engage-Disengage, Look at That, Emergency U-Turn, Circle Back,
                Threshold Recovery — every game is designed to build skills
                while staying sub-threshold. No generic "just feed treats."
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Benefit 4 -->
        <div
          class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-md border-l-4 border-blue-500 hover:shadow-xl transition"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0">
              <svg
                class="w-8 h-8 text-blue-500"
                fill="currentColor"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
              >
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Dog & People Reactivity Protocols
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Field training setups, stuffed animal desensitization for
                extreme cases, progression tables for beginner → intermediate →
                advanced scenarios. We cover <strong>both</strong> triggers.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Benefit 5 -->
        <div
          class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-md border-l-4 border-blue-500 hover:shadow-xl transition"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0">
              <svg
                class="w-8 h-8 text-blue-500"
                fill="currentColor"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
              >
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                4 Real-World Walking Scenarios
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Dog approaching on sidewalk. Jogger passing from behind.
                Multiple dogs at a fence. Surprise trigger from a blind corner.
                Step-by-step game plans so you know <em>exactly</em> what to do.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Benefit 6 -->
        <div
          class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-md border-l-4 border-blue-500 hover:shadow-xl transition"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0">
              <svg
                class="w-8 h-8 text-blue-500"
                fill="currentColor"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
              >
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Advanced Handler Insights
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Why your energy matters. Why one bad exposure undoes three good
                ones. Why progress isn't linear. The truths most trainers won't
                tell you — because they take years to learn.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-12 p-6 bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 rounded-r-2xl"
      >
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-800">
          <strong
            >This is the protocol we use with reactive dogs in our Board & Train
            programs</strong
          > — now available as a free starting point for Virginia families who want
          to do the work themselves.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DOWNLOAD FORM SECTION -->
    <section class="mb-20" id="download-form">
      <div
        class="max-w-2xl mx-auto bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-blue-600 p-8 md:p-12 rounded-3xl shadow-2xl"
      >
        <div class="text-center mb-8">
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
            Get Your Free Reset Planner Now
          </h2>
          <p class="text-white/90 text-lg">
            Enter your information below and we'll send the Reactive Dog Reset
            Planner straight to your inbox.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- PLACEHOLDER: You'll replace this with your actual Tally form -->
        <iframe
          data-tally-src="https://tally.so/embed/LZpjop?alignLeft=1&hideTitle=1&transparentBackground=1&dynamicHeight=1"
          loading="lazy"
          width="100%"
          height="682"
          frameborder="0"
          marginheight="0"
          marginwidth="0"
          title="Reactive Dog Reset Planner"></iframe>
        <script>
          var d = document,
            w = "https://tally.so/widgets/embed.js",
            v = function () {
              "undefined" != typeof Tally
                ? Tally.loadEmbeds()
                : d
                    .querySelectorAll("iframe[data-tally-src]:not([src])")
                    .forEach(function (e) {
                      e.src = e.dataset.tallySrc;
                    });
            };
          if ("undefined" != typeof Tally) v();
          else if (d.querySelector('script[src="' + w + '"]') == null) {
            var s = d.createElement("script");
            ((s.src = w),
              (s.onload = v),
              (s.onerror = v),
              d.body.appendChild(s));
          }
        </script>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 4: Who This Is For -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2
          class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 text-center mb-12"
        >
          This Guide Is For You If:
        </h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div
            class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-md border-2 border-blue-200 hover:border-blue-400 transition"
          >
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-3xl">🐕</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-lg text-gray-800">
                Your dog <strong>explodes at other dogs or people</strong> on walks
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-md border-2 border-blue-200 hover:border-blue-400 transition"
          >
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-3xl">🐕</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-lg text-gray-800">
                You've tried <strong>"just feed treats"</strong> and it didn't work
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-md border-2 border-blue-200 hover:border-blue-400 transition"
          >
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-3xl">🐕</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-lg text-gray-800">
                You're <strong>exhausted</strong> from avoiding triggers and feeling
                trapped
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-md border-2 border-blue-200 hover:border-blue-400 transition"
          >
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-3xl">🐕</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-lg text-gray-800">
                You want a <strong>science-based protocol</strong> — not YouTube tips
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-md border-2 border-blue-200 hover:border-blue-400 transition md:col-span-2"
          >
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-3xl">🐕</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-lg text-gray-800">
                You're ready to <strong>put in the work</strong> to rebuild your dog's
                confidence and regulation
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Final CTA -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <div
        class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center bg-gray-900 text-white p-12 rounded-3xl"
      >
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">
          Ready to Stop Fighting and Start Training?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl mb-8 text-gray-200">
          Download your free planner and get the exact protocol we use with
          reactive dogs in our Board & Train programs.
        </p>
        <a
          href="#download-form"
          class="inline-block bg-blue-500 text-white font-bold px-10 py-5 rounded-full hover:bg-blue-400 transition transform hover:scale-105 shadow-xl text-lg"
        >
          Get the Free Planner
        </a>

        <div class="mt-10 pt-10 border-t border-gray-700">
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            <strong>Need Hands-On Help?</strong>
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">
            Our Board & Train programs include intensive behavior modification
            for reactive dogs — plus handler transfer coaching so the progress
            sticks.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://leashlegacyk9.com/contact/"
            class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 font-semibold underline"
          >
            Learn About Our Reactive Dog Programs →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</MainLayout>
